T1  - Administrative Experimentation: A Methodology for More Rigorous “Muddling Through”
AU  - Berlin, Victor N.
Y1  - 1978/04/01
PY  - 1978
DA  - 1978/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.24.8.789
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.24.8.789
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 789
EP  - 799
VL  - 24
IS  - 8
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Administrative experimentation is described as a more rigorous approach to the ?muddling through? style of managerial decision making. It includes a class of heuristics for obtaining feedback on management decisions in what amounts to a continuous trial and error process. A manager on his own, a manager-consultant team, or a manager-researcher team can implement these heuristics in a variety of settings to serve a variety of purposes. A case study describing one application of this approach is presented.
AB  - Administrative experimentation is described as a more rigorous approach to the ?muddling through? style of managerial decision making. It includes a class of heuristics for obtaining feedback on management decisions in what amounts to a continuous trial and error process. A manager on his own, a manager-consultant team, or a manager-researcher team can implement these heuristics in a variety of settings to serve a variety of purposes. A case study describing one application of this approach is presented.
